Like he said.

795
01:16:50,650 --> 01:16:52,600
(Music thumps)

796
01:16:59,320 --> 01:17:01,280
Good God.

797
01:17:01,360 --> 01:17:02,610
I can't drink all that.

798
01:17:02,700 --> 01:17:05,740
No, but I know a man who can.

799
01:17:13,130 --> 01:17:14,630
Cheers.

800
01:17:17,380 --> 01:17:19,870
Since when did you start smoking those?

801
01:17:19,970 --> 01:17:21,550
What happened to your roll-ups?

802
01:17:29,480 --> 01:17:31,850
Oh, Jesus. Make my next one a double.

803
01:17:34,400 --> 01:17:37,110
# When I was a young man

804
01:17:37,190 --> 01:17:39,530
# I used to dream of a maiden...

805
01:17:41,320 --> 01:17:42,570
That's my song.

806
01:17:42,700 --> 01:17:45,070
# With long soft hair

807
01:17:46,200 --> 01:17:48,830
# Blowing in the wind

808
01:17:51,870 --> 01:17:57,170
# Her laughing eyes
and loving arms would follow

809
01:17:59,840 --> 01:18:01,840
# When I'd sail around the world...

810
01:18:01,920 --> 01:18:04,300
Hey, Frankie. Hey, Frankie.

811
01:18:04,390 --> 01:18:09,730
I bet you all your trump cards
that you don't ask Catriona Murray to dance.

812
01:18:11,230 --> 01:18:14,890
# I'd ride down on a great white horse...

813
01:18:16,060 --> 01:18:19,320
If you do that, I'll get your mum up to dance.

814
01:18:20,650 --> 01:18:22,190
Deal?

815
01:18:23,950 --> 01:18:26,700
# I'd bring her laughter...

816
01:18:26,780 --> 01:18:28,030
Dance?

817
01:18:28,120 --> 01:18:30,580
# On a rainy day...

818
01:18:30,660 --> 01:18:32,620
I never dance.

819
01:18:33,750 --> 01:18:37,210
You'll have to this once.
Frankie's made another bet.

820
01:18:38,880 --> 01:18:42,170
You'd better watch him.
It's becoming a bit of a habit.

821
01:18:50,600 --> 01:18:55,890
# When I was a young girl,
I used to dream of a lover

822
01:18:59,270 --> 01:19:05,730
# Who'd be my shining knight
of strength one day

823
01:19:07,280 --> 01:19:12,530
# He'd take me to a castle in the heavens

824
01:19:15,830 --> 01:19:22,200
# And battle all my dragons on the way

825
01:19:23,130 --> 01:19:30,260
# And he'd ride down on a great white horse

826
01:19:31,640 --> 01:19:35,140
# He'd give me love

827
01:19:35,230 --> 01:19:38,690
# I'd been longing for

828
01:19:39,690 --> 01:19:43,640
# He'd bring me joy

829
01:19:43,740 --> 01:19:47,950
# And lasting peace

830
01:19:48,030 --> 01:19:52,070
# And on a great white horse

831
01:19:52,160 --> 01:19:55,040
# He'd ride away with me...

832
01:20:13,890 --> 01:20:15,850
(Cheering and applause)

833
01:20:15,930 --> 01:20:19,480
ALLY: Uno, dos, tres, cuatro.

834
01:20:19,770 --> 01:20:23,440
Uno, dos, tres, cuatro!

835
01:20:23,520 --> 01:20:24,860
(Laughter)

836
01:20:24,940 --> 01:20:26,900
I had a good time tonight.

837
01:20:30,110 --> 01:20:32,070
Don't sound so surprised.

838
01:20:34,620 --> 01:20:37,410
You are the best!

839
01:20:37,500 --> 01:20:39,460
He's got your eyes.

840
01:20:42,750 --> 01:20:44,340
They pull you.

841
01:20:45,380 --> 01:20:46,630
Right in.

842
01:20:46,710 --> 01:20:49,670
Uno, dos, tres, cuatro.

843
01:20:49,760 --> 01:20:51,720
I don't know what to say to that.

844
01:20:52,970 --> 01:20:55,010
Well, you don't have to say anything.

845
01:20:59,520 --> 01:21:01,270
You don't have to say nice things to me.

846
01:21:01,350 --> 01:21:03,310
I'm not paying you for that.

847
01:21:05,780 --> 01:21:07,730
So, why don't you want to hear them?

848
01:21:10,780 --> 01:21:12,740
What are you afraid of?

849
01:21:16,160 --> 01:21:18,120
Where did Marie find you?

850
01:21:20,160 --> 01:21:21,870
No.

851
01:21:22,920 --> 01:21:24,880
I thought we agreed: No history.

852
01:21:32,340 --> 01:21:34,300
Things have changed.

853
01:21:38,180 --> 01:21:39,720
Have they?

854
01:21:44,360 --> 01:21:48,730
What I find really difficult...

855
01:21:50,240 --> 01:21:52,190
to understand...

856
01:21:53,410 --> 01:21:54,950
is why?

857
01:21:57,290 --> 01:21:59,370
I told you why. Frankie made a bet.

858
01:21:59,450 --> 01:22:02,000
No, no, no, no, no.

859
01:22:02,080 --> 01:22:06,540
Why did he ever leave the two of you?

860
01:22:12,800 --> 01:22:15,130
He didn't leave us. I left him.

861
01:22:18,260 --> 01:22:21,890
One night I just picked Frankie up, and I left.

862
01:22:21,980 --> 01:22:25,140
And my mother came with me,
to make sure I never went back.

863
01:22:28,860 --> 01:22:30,730
And we've been leaving ever since.

864
01:22:30,820 --> 01:22:33,860
<i>Always ready in case he shows up.</i>

865
01:22:41,000 --> 01:22:44,780
Frankie wasn't born deaf.
It was a present from his daddy.

866
01:23:12,900 --> 01:23:16,530
Frankie's a very... very lucky boy.

867
01:23:19,870 --> 01:23:22,440
How do you figure that one out?

868
01:23:22,540 --> 01:23:25,330
I'm his mother, and I lie to him every single day.

869
01:23:25,420 --> 01:23:27,000
No.

870
01:23:28,710 --> 01:23:30,710
No, you protect him every single day.

871
01:23:36,220 --> 01:23:37,300
Do I?

872
01:23:44,930 --> 01:23:50,440
Every time I write one of those letters
I promise myself it'll be the last one.

873
01:23:52,280 --> 01:23:54,850
<i>I thought he'd lose interest, in time.</i>

874
01:23:55,990 --> 01:23:57,530
<i>Just stop</i>

875
01:24:00,490 --> 01:24:02,830
But see, if he hasn't written
for a couple of weeks,

876
01:24:02,910 --> 01:24:06,200
I'm the one egging him on,
telling him to hurry up and write.

877
01:24:09,130 --> 01:24:11,170
<i>It's the only way I can hear his voice.</i>

878
01:24:58,680 --> 01:25:00,090
<i>I'd better go.</i>

879
01:25:01,800 --> 01:25:03,300
I'm away first thing.

880
01:25:07,600 --> 01:25:09,270
Can I say goodbye?

881
01:25:09,350 --> 01:25:11,020
If you can wake him.

882
01:25:52,400 --> 01:25:53,850
Hey.

883
01:25:56,770 --> 01:25:59,350
(Uses voice) You're coming back?

884
01:26:04,820 --> 01:26:06,950
I don't know, Frankie.

885
01:26:35,520 --> 01:26:36,640
Did you do this?

886
01:26:41,860 --> 01:26:44,400
Frankie, I can't take this. This... This is yours.

887
01:26:45,490 --> 01:26:47,320
(Mouths)

888
01:26:53,210 --> 01:26:55,160
I'd be honoured to take it.

889
01:26:57,710 --> 01:26:59,500
It's beautiful.

890
01:27:10,520 --> 01:27:12,470
Remember, Frankie.

891
01:27:13,850 --> 01:27:15,810
We're all connected.

892
01:30:36,140 --> 01:30:38,100
Lizzie, Lizzie.

893
01:30:47,520 --> 01:30:49,230
I've let myself go a wee bit. Sorry.

894
01:30:54,490 --> 01:30:56,410
It's been a long time.

895
01:31:01,580 --> 01:31:03,250
You're still beautiful.

896
01:31:04,460 --> 01:31:06,950
No, I'm not. I'm not beautiful.

897
01:31:08,040 --> 01:31:09,840
I'm sorry.

898
01:31:13,170 --> 01:31:15,090
I'm sorry, Lizzie.

899
01:31:16,180 --> 01:31:17,890
I'm sorry, Lizzie.

900
01:31:17,970 --> 01:31:20,140
Shush, Davey. Shush.

901
01:31:22,140 --> 01:31:24,980
It's all right. It's all right now.

902
01:31:26,690 --> 01:31:28,150
Don't cry.

903
01:31:34,150 --> 01:31:35,650
Where's Frankie?

904
01:31:35,740 --> 01:31:37,820
<i>He's at school.</i>

905
01:31:37,910 --> 01:31:40,780
He's nine now, nearly ten.

906
01:31:40,870 --> 01:31:42,450
Aye, I know.

907
01:31:45,250 --> 01:31:47,370
He's top at geography.

908
01:31:48,840 --> 01:31:50,790
I always knew he was clever.

909
01:31:53,590 --> 01:31:55,300
Must take that off you.

910
01:31:55,380 --> 01:31:59,250
I don't think so. You were the one
that could have gone to college.

911
01:32:33,300 --> 01:32:35,630
I want to see him, Lizzie.

912
01:32:35,720 --> 01:32:37,970
I've got a right to see him.

913
01:32:38,050 --> 01:32:40,260
<i>- Don't give me that.
- It's too late for fighting.</i>

914
01:32:40,350 --> 01:32:42,140
<i>Just let me see him.</i>

915
01:32:44,180 --> 01:32:46,140
I want him to know how sorry I am.

916
01:32:48,520 --> 01:32:49,980
He's my son.

917
01:32:50,060 --> 01:32:52,020
He's not your son. He's mine.

918
01:32:54,280 --> 01:32:56,610
You don't deserve him.

919
01:32:56,690 --> 01:32:59,530
You don't deserve his forgiveness.

920
01:33:02,120 --> 01:33:03,700
Christ.

921
01:33:06,200 --> 01:33:08,160
I made one mistake.

922
01:33:09,920 --> 01:33:13,170
One stupid fucking mistake,
and you made me pay.

923
01:33:13,250 --> 01:33:15,630
<i>You've made me pay, all right.</i>

924
01:33:16,800 --> 01:33:18,800
You're a bitch.

925
01:33:19,880 --> 01:33:22,970
<i>You're nothing but a bitch!</i>

926
01:33:24,470 --> 01:33:25,750
I want to see my son!

927
01:33:28,430 --> 01:33:29,810
<i>I've got a right!</i>

928
01:33:29,890 --> 01:33:31,480
I'm his father!

929
01:33:31,560 --> 01:33:33,230
<i>I've got rights!</i>

930
01:33:33,310 --> 01:33:36,270
I've got my rights! I'm his father!

931
01:33:36,360 --> 01:33:37,940
You're not his father!

932
01:33:38,030 --> 01:33:41,280
He's got a different father now, a real father.

933
01:33:41,360 --> 01:33:46,280
A kind, gentle man, who teaches him
to throw stones across the water.

934
01:33:46,370 --> 01:33:48,200
You could never be his father.

935
01:33:48,290 --> 01:33:50,250
I want to see my son!

936
01:33:50,330 --> 01:33:52,670
<i>- Davey, please, no, come on.
- I'm his father!</i>

937
01:33:52,750 --> 01:33:53,860
Davey, no, stop it.

938
01:33:53,960 --> 01:33:55,240
Nurse!

939
01:33:55,340 --> 01:33:57,340
<i>Nurse!</i>

940
01:33:57,460 --> 01:33:59,340
I want to see my son!

941
01:34:12,900 --> 01:34:14,850
Lizzie, wait a minute.

942
01:34:16,770 --> 01:34:19,780
Lizzie, Lizzie, please.

943
01:34:19,860 --> 01:34:22,270
He nearly killed us, Janet!

944
01:34:22,360 --> 01:34:24,450
I know. I know.

945
01:34:25,450 --> 01:34:27,490
He's only got a few days left.

946
01:34:27,580 --> 01:34:29,490
He can't touch you now.

947
01:34:30,370 --> 01:34:32,290
Let him die in peace.

948
01:34:33,080 --> 01:34:35,040
For your own sake.

949
01:35:09,790 --> 01:35:12,160
I want to talk to you. It's very important.

950
01:35:14,330 --> 01:35:16,290
I got a message today from your dad.

951
01:35:19,590 --> 01:35:21,960
He's not very well, Frankie.

952
01:35:22,050 --> 01:35:23,590
He's very, very sick.

953
01:35:26,340 --> 01:35:28,800
But he says he wants you to know he loves you.

954
01:35:30,890 --> 01:35:32,060
Very much.

955
01:36:04,920 --> 01:36:08,260
<i>Dear Da, I thought you'd like this drawing.</i>

956
01:36:08,340 --> 01:36:10,680
<i>I copied it from my book.</i>

957
01:36:10,760 --> 01:36:13,170
<i>Ma says you're not very well.</i>

958
01:36:13,270 --> 01:36:15,560
<i>I hope you feel better soon.</i>

959
01:36:15,640 --> 01:36:17,600
<i>Love from your son, Frankie.</i>

960
01:36:49,800 --> 01:36:51,760
<i>DOCTOR: OK, call the crash team.</i>

961
01:36:54,680 --> 01:36:57,170
Please! What is wrong with him?

962
01:36:57,270 --> 01:36:59,390
Let's get the bed down. Come on.

963
01:37:00,480 --> 01:37:02,440
Mrs Morrison?

964
01:37:02,520 --> 01:37:06,110
It might be best if you went
and had a cup of tea just now.

965
01:37:06,190 --> 01:37:09,650
I'll send someone along to find you
as soon as we have any news.

966
01:37:10,740 --> 01:37:12,700
This is for my husband.

967
01:37:13,950 --> 01:37:15,330
It's from our son.

968
01:37:15,410 --> 01:37:16,990
Right.

969
01:37:21,710 --> 01:37:23,500
- Oh, Nurse, erm...
- Yes?

970
01:37:28,010 --> 01:37:29,510
Could you make sure he sees it?

971
01:37:29,590 --> 01:37:31,260
I'll make sure.

972
01:37:41,350 --> 01:37:45,020
<i>LIZZIE: Davey Morrison
died peacefully after a long illness.</i>

973
01:37:45,110 --> 01:37:47,110
<i>Father to Frankie.</i>

974
01:38:19,730 --> 01:38:23,890
I know it's a terrible thing to say,
but Davey's finally done you a favour.

975
01:38:23,980 --> 01:38:25,730
It's over now.

976
01:38:29,570 --> 01:38:30,820
Marie?

977
01:38:30,900 --> 01:38:32,180
What?

978
01:38:33,240 --> 01:38:35,030
Who was he?

979
01:38:36,410 --> 01:38:38,160
My brother.

980
01:38:41,120 --> 01:38:42,870
Oh, right.

981
01:38:46,000 --> 01:38:47,960
I've got to go.

982
01:38:50,590 --> 01:38:52,920
- Where are you going?
- I'll see you after.

983
01:38:57,350 --> 01:38:59,010
<i>MAN: Do you want me to check the box?</i>

984
01:38:59,100 --> 01:39:01,060
<i>LIZZIE: There won't be anything in it.</i>

985
01:39:01,140 --> 01:39:03,720
<i>It'll cost you to have your mail forwarded.</i>

986
01:39:03,810 --> 01:39:06,520
I'll check it for you, hen,
just to be on the safe side.

987
01:39:54,820 --> 01:39:57,280
<i>FRANKIE: Thanks for the book.</i>

988
01:39:57,370 --> 01:40:00,320
<i>I've read it all the way through now twice.</i>

989
01:40:02,330 --> 01:40:04,080
<i>I took it into school.</i>

990
01:40:04,160 --> 01:40:05,750
<i>I know you won't mind.</i>

991
01:40:05,830 --> 01:40:07,870
<i>My teacher put it on the nature table.</i>

992
01:40:20,810 --> 01:40:22,350
(Low whistle)

993
01:40:22,430 --> 01:40:25,010
<i>Miss Mackenzie gave me a gold star.</i>

994
01:40:25,100 --> 01:40:28,270
<i>I've got eight now. Catriona's got 20.</i>

995
01:40:28,350 --> 01:40:31,690
<i>Ricky's only got one, and it's not even gold.</i>

996
01:40:39,070 --> 01:40:40,240
<i>Guess what.</i>

997
01:40:40,320 --> 01:40:42,200
<i>I got into the football team.</i>

998
01:40:42,290 --> 01:40:45,370
<i>Well, the reserves. I'm playing on Saturday.</i>

999
01:40:45,460 --> 01:40:47,950
<i>And guess what else.</i>

1000
01:40:48,040 --> 01:40:50,210
<i>I got one wrong in geography this week.</i>

1001
01:40:54,340 --> 01:40:56,340
<i>Ma and I had a bit of a shock last week.</i>

1002
01:40:57,510 --> 01:41:01,340
<i>My da - my real da - he's been sick.</i>

1003
01:41:02,510 --> 01:41:04,970
<i>I think he's been sick for a long time.</i>

1004
01:41:05,060 --> 01:41:06,720
<i>Ma never said anything.</i>

1005
01:41:06,810 --> 01:41:08,390
<i>But I just knew.</i>

1006
01:41:08,480 --> 01:41:11,850
<i>And last week, he died.</i>

1007
01:41:11,940 --> 01:41:14,190
<i>I think ma's very sad, inside.</i>

1008
01:41:14,280 --> 01:41:16,190
<i>But Marie says time's a great healer,</i>

1009
01:41:16,280 --> 01:41:20,200
<i>and Ma's not to worry any more,
cos she's still got me.</i>

1010
01:41:21,200 --> 01:41:23,820
<i>Anyway, I've got to go now. My tea's ready.</i>

1011
01:41:23,910 --> 01:41:26,200
<i>I hope it's not chips.</i>

1012
01:41:26,290 --> 01:41:28,250
<i>I've had them three times this week.</i>

1013
01:41:29,710 --> 01:41:33,080
<i>Maybe you'll come and see us one more time.</i>

1014
01:41:33,170 --> 01:41:35,340
